{"type": "assistant", "message": {"model": "claude-sonnet-4-6", "id": "msg_vrtx_01E3i4hijhn8WAkbtB5Qxx49", "type": "message", "role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "thinking", "thinking": "Now I have a complete picture:\n- The existing `nielsens-heuristics-jagged-edge.md` is about an intern experiment comparing AI tools using Nielsen's heuristics \u2014 it's NOT a canonical reference page for the heuristics themselves.\n- There's NO dedicated canonical reference page for Nielsen's 10 Usability Heuristics.\n- The new article content is directly from nngroup.com about the 10 heuristics themselves.\n- **Overlap is LOW** \u2014 create a new page.\n\nI should create a new page `nielsens-10-usability-heuristics.md` with a canonical reference to the heuristics.\nNow I need to plan the updates: create the new wiki page, then add cross-links to the jagged-edge experiment, the UX quality rubric, and the evaluator agent since they all reference these heuristics, plus update the index to surface the new canonical reference.\n\nI'm also mapping connections to active projects\u2014the automated usability testing tool directly applies these heuristics, the evaluator agent uses them for scoring, and the prototype creator considers usability dimensions.\n\nI have the core content from the article: the ten heuristics covering system visibility, language matching, user control, consistency, error prevention, and more\u2014though the last one got cut off mid-description.\n\nThe remaining heuristics focus on minimizing memory load, supporting both novice and expert users, keeping design minimal and focused, providing clear error recovery, and offering searchable documentation when needed. These were originally developed with Rolf Molich back in 1990 and refined a few years later.\n\nNow I'm setting up the wiki page with a concise slug and identifying cross-links to related work \u2014 including applications of these heuristics in AI model comparisons, usability rubrics, automated evaluation systems, and testing frameworks.\n\nI'll write the new page, then update the existing cross-references in the related documents to point to this canonical resource.", "signature": ""}], "stop_reason": null, "stop_sequence": null, "stop_details": null, "usage": {"input_tokens": 1, "cache_creation_input_tokens": 7150, "cache_read_input_tokens": 43297, "cache_creation": {"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens": 7150, "ephemeral_1h_input_tokens": 0}, "output_tokens": 8}, "context_management": null}, "parent_tool_use_id": null, "session_id": "6105c313-2c53-4f04-88a6-2b3c3c60cfc6", "uuid": "59791f1f-f338-4f8f-afe1-2f627a6b3293", "request_id": "req_vrtx_011Ccrm9yVjV8iomFUCTnhpf", "timestamp": "2026-07-09T16:00:37.449Z"}
