{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_vrtx_015LiKWMufS2fhrbpBon9uvw","type":"tool_result","content":"The file /Users/ejaquez/second-brain/wiki/ux-quality-rubric.md has been updated successfully. (file state is current in your context — no need to Read it back)"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"6105c313-2c53-4f04-88a6-2b3c3c60cfc6","uuid":"f2b438bf-5e34-4e8c-ac34-4ed3fdbd5435","timestamp":"2026-07-09T16:00:58.941Z","tool_use_result":{"filePath":"/Users/ejaquez/second-brain/wiki/ux-quality-rubric.md","oldString":"- [Nielsen's Heuristics & The Jagged Edge](nielsens-heuristics-jagged-edge.md) — informs the usability dimension","newString":"- [Nielsen's 10 Usability Heuristics](nielsens-10-usability-heuristics.md) — canonical reference for the 10 heuristics underlying the usability dimension\n- [Nielsen's Heuristics & The Jagged Edge](nielsens-heuristics-jagged-edge.md) — informs the usability dimension via AI model comparison","originalFile":"# UX Quality Rubric\n\nThe scoring system used by [Prototype Creator](prototype-creator.md) to evaluate generated prototypes. Scored by a restricted `prototype-scorer` agent (no shell, no network, no MCP).\n\n## Dimensions (0–2 each, 8 total)\n\n| Dimension | What It Measures |\n|---|---|\n| **Completeness** | Does the prototype cover the RFE's user stories and acceptance criteria? |\n| **Usability** | Is the interaction pattern clear and free of obvious friction? (Nielsen's 10 heuristics) |\n| **Feasibility** | Can this be built with the target design system (PatternFly 6)? |\n| **Fidelity Match** | Does the prototype match the requested fidelity level — not over or under-engineered? |\n\n## Pass Threshold\n\n6+ total with no zeros. Prototypes scoring above get `prototype-creator-rubric-pass`. Below get `prototype-creator-needs-attention`.\n\n## Scoring Agent\n\nOne invocation per dimension ensures scores are deterministic and auditable. The scorer agent is restricted — no shell, no network, no MCP — to prevent contamination.\n\n## Connection to Evaluator Super Agent\n\nThe [Evaluator Super Agent](evaluator-super-agent.md) will extend this rubric with additional dimensions from simulated usability and desirability testing. See also [Nielsen's Heuristics](nielsens-heuristics-jagged-edge.md) for the research that informs the usability dimension.\n\n## Related\n\n- [Prototype Creator](prototype-creator.md) — the pipeline that uses this rubric\n- [Evaluator Super Agent](evaluator-super-agent.md) — extends this scoring\n- [Nielsen's Heuristics & The Jagged Edge](nielsens-heuristics-jagged-edge.md) — informs the usability dimension\n- [Agent Eval Harness](agent-eval-harness.md) — similar pattern of rubric-based automated scoring\n- [Weekly Design Sync — July 1](weekly-design-sync-2026-07-01.md) — scoring dimensions flagged for revisit at next meeting\n\n## Sources\n\n- sources/2026-06-09-prototype-creator-overview.html\n- andybraren/prototype-creator config/ux-rubric.yaml\n","structuredPatch":[{"oldStart":27,"oldLines":7,"newStart":27,"newLines":8,"lines":[" "," - [Prototype Creator](prototype-creator.md) — the pipeline that uses this rubric"," - [Evaluator Super Agent](evaluator-super-agent.md) — extends this scoring","-- [Nielsen's Heuristics & The Jagged Edge](nielsens-heuristics-jagged-edge.md) — informs the usability dimension","+- [Nielsen's 10 Usability Heuristics](nielsens-10-usability-heuristics.md) — canonical reference for the 10 heuristics underlying the usability dimension","+- [Nielsen's Heuristics & The Jagged Edge](nielsens-heuristics-jagged-edge.md) — informs the usability dimension via AI model comparison"," - [Agent Eval Harness](agent-eval-harness.md) — similar pattern of rubric-based automated scoring"," - [Weekly Design Sync — July 1](weekly-design-sync-2026-07-01.md) — scoring dimensions flagged for revisit at next meeting"," "]}],"userModified":false,"replaceAll":false}}
