gential).\n\n## 2026-06-22 — Ingested: RH AI-First UX Meeting (June 18)\n- Created: rh-ai-first-ux-2026-06-18.md — Weekly team meeting: Fable AI impressions, Jobs-to-be-Done PR passing review, GitLab pages routing fix, Evan's prototype-evaluate demo, Outcome Creator project plan, Jira SDLC migration, designer enablement planned\n- Cross-linked with: prototype-creator.md, evaluator-super-agent.md, outcome-tiger-team.md, ai-sdlc-pipeline.md\n- Category: Meetings\n\n## 2026-06-22 — Ingested: Ansible AI Helpers Strategy Meeting (June 17)\n\n- Created: ansible-ai-helpers-strategy-2026-06-17.md — Strategy session on integrating UXD AI Helpers with Ansible's Carbonite harness; heuristic eval selected as pilot, centralized repo via MRs, June 30 leadership presentation\n- Cross-linked with: ai-sdlc-pipeline.md, agent-eval-harness.md, prototype-creator.md, nielsens-heuristics-jagged-edge.md, evaluator-super-agent.md\n- Category: Meetings\n\n## 2026-06-16 — Updated: My Cursor Claw (Week 4 growth)\n\n**Updated:** my-cursor-claw.md — expanded from 12 to 20+ skills, added 5th MCP (Slack), added Automated Daily Review System section documenting the 3-checkpoint launchd infrastructure (morning/midday/EOD with Apple Reminders, progress doc auto-update).\n\n**New skills documented:** second-brain-ingest, work-context, meeting-prep, standup-writer, session-log, sprint-manager, critique, doc-sync, humanize-text, superpowers, skill-guide.\n\n**Index updated:** My Cursor Claw entry updated to reflect current scope.\n\n## 2026-06-09 — Initial wiki seeding\n\n**Sources ingested:**\n- sources/2026-06-09-prototype-creator-overview.html\n- sources/2026-06-03-nielsen-agents-task1.html\n- sources/2026-06-04-agent-eval-harness-overview.html\n- sources/2026-06-05-skill-eval-cheat-sheet.html\n- Andy/Evan meeting notes (2026-06-08, Google Drive)\n- jnemargut/decision-kit README (GitHub)\n- opendatahub-io/rfe-creator README (GitHub)\n- andybraren/prototype-creator README + CLAUDE.md (GitHub)\n\n**Pages created (9):**\n- prototype-creator.md — Phase 2 of AI-SDLC, prototype generation pipeline\n- ai-sdlc-pipeline.md — three-phase pipeline overview (rfe → prototype → strat)\n- decision-kit.md — Decision Driven Development toolkit, 24 skills\n- agent-eval-harness.md — skill quality evaluation framework\n- nielsens-heuristics-jagged-edge.md — first internship task, AI model comparison\n- my-cursor-claw.md — personal workspace with 12 skills and 4 MCP connections\n- ux-quality-rubric.md — 4-dimension prototype scoring system\n- evaluator-super-agent.md — upcoming assignment, automated prototype evaluation\n- rfe-creator.md — Phase 1 of AI-SDLC, RFE creation and assessment\n\n**Cross-links established:** All 9 pages interlinked based on topical relationships. Key connections: prototype-creator ↔ decision-kit (integration), evaluator-super-agent ↔ agent-eval-harness (pattern reuse), nielsens-heuristics ↔ evaluator-super-agent (methodology).\n\n**Index updated:** 3 categories created (Red Hat AI-SDLC, Evaluation & Quality, Tools & Skills).\n\n## 2026-06-09 — Ingested: Prototype Creator Demo Transcript (May 14)\n\n**Source:** sources/2026-05-14-prototype-creator-demo-transcript.md — ~2 hour recorded walkthrough by Andy Braren with Beau Morley and Dash Copeland\n\n**Created:** prototype-creator-demo-may14.md — Comprehensive summary covering both automated/speedrun and human-in-the-loop workflows, git submodule integration, preview URLs, token usage, and extensive team discussion on designer workflow, outcome-level prototyping, and the vision for tools beyond Cursor.\n\n**Cross-linked with:** prototype-creator.md (added demo reference), evaluator-super-agent.md (added \"Key Design Inputs from Demo\" section with 5 actionable insights: scope to NEW elements, generate decision pages in auto mode, outcome-level awareness, preview URL as eval entry point, token efficiency)\n\n**Category:** Red Hat AI-SDLC\n\n## 2026-06-09 — Ingested: Proposal for an Outcome Tiger Team\n\n**Source:** sources/2026-06-09-outcome-tiger-team-proposal.pdf — Andy Braren's proposal for agentic outcome creation, prioritization, and visualization. 3 workstreams: outcome creation, E2E prototype validation, outcome prioritization aid (\"Leaderboard of Pain\").\n\n**Created:** outcome-tiger-team.md — Comprehensive summary covering the problem (RFEs/STRATs disconnected from outcomes), three workstreams mapped to benefits, pipeline extension diagram, and direct connections to the evaluator super agent's outcome-level awareness requirement.\n\n**Cross-linked with:** ai-sdlc-pipeline.md (added outcomes as upstream step in flow diagram), prototype-creator.md (added Workstream 2 E2E validation link), evaluator-super-agent.md (added outcome-level awareness connection), rfe-creator.md (added Workstream 1 pattern reuse link)\n\n**Category:** Red Hat AI-SDLC\n\n## 2026-06-15 — Session Log\n\n**Sessions:** 4 agent conversations\n\n**Created:** session-log-2026-06-15.md — Built work-context, meeting-prep, standup-writer, and session-log skills; created sprint-manager; crafted prototype-evaluate Slack response; updated internship progress doc.\n\n**Tags:** #daily-log #2026-06-15 #skills #canvas #second-brain #prototype-creator\n\n**Files created/modified:** 8 files across 5 skills, 1 canvas, 1 script\n\n**Cross-linked with:** my-cursor-claw.md, prototype-creator.md, agent-eval-harness.md, evaluator-super-agent.md\n\n**Category:** Session Logs\n\n## 2026-06-16 — Session Log\n\n**Sessions:** 4 agent conversations\n\n**Signal:** 2 important items, 0 stale carry-forwards\n\n**Created:** session-log-2026-06-16.md — Shipped second brain smart check-ins (importance scoring, carry-forward, auto-resolve); created critique, humanize-text, doc-sync, superpowers, trend-scan skills; GitHub README redesign research.\n\n**Tags:** #daily-log #2026-06-16 #zack #shipped #skills #second-brain #github\n\n**Files created/modified:** 7 files across 6 skills, 1 config\n\n**Cross-linked with:** my-cursor-claw.md, decision-kit.md, agent-eval-harness.md\n\n**Category:** Session Logs\n\n## 2026-06-16 — Ingested: Red Hat AI-First Lessons (Jeremy Eder)\n\n**Source:** ~/Desktop/Second Brain Inbox/redhat-ai-first-lessons v2.pdf — 38-slide deck on agentic SDLC, issue-to-PR bots, eval infrastructure, AgentReady, and organizational change.\n\n**Created:** redhat-ai-first-lessons.md — Comprehensive summary covering the 6-phase agentic SDLC, autonomous bugfix bot metrics (22-minute median issue-to-PR), evaluation fundamentals (datasets, runners, judges), context engineering principles, and AgentReady repo assessment tool.\n\n**Cross-linked with:** ai-sdlc-pipeline.md, agent-eval-harness.md, evaluator-super-agent.md, prototype-creator.md, rfe-creator.md\n\n**Category:** Red Hat AI-SDLC\n\n## 2026-06-16 — Ingested: Andy/Evan Evaluation Review Meeting\n\n- Created: andy-evan-eval-review-2026-06-16.md — Outcomes grounding, super evaluator architecture, overlay approach, hint mechanism, screenshot consolidation\n- Cross-linked with: evaluator-super-agent.md, prototype-creator.md, outcome-tiger-team.md, ux-quality-rubric.md, ai-sdlc-pipeline.md\n- Category: Meetings\n- Also created: Obsidian note (01-Meetings/2026-06/) + HTML report (Notes Export/)\n\n## 2026-06-16 — Ingested: Cursor Work Summary (June 16)\n\n**Source:** ~/Desktop/Second Brain Inbox/2026-06-16-cursor-work-summary.md — Daily summary of 4 agent sessions.\n\n**Created:** cursor-work-2026-06-16.md — Record of trend-scan, batch skill creation, GitHub README, and second brain smart check-ins work.\n\n**Cross-linked with:** my-cursor-claw.md, decision-kit.md, agent-eval-harness.md, session-log-2026-06-16.md\n\n**Category:** Daily Work Logs\n\n## 2026-07-09 — Ingested: Weekly Design Sync (July 1, 2026)\n\n- Created: weekly-design-sync-2026-07-01.md — Team sync with Andy Braren, Evan, Zack Bodnar: evaluator demo set for next week, PatternFly 6 migration Q3 target, Nielsen's heuristics adopted as base rubric, scoring dimens